content:
Configure Publish Options on a FlexCard

You must activate your FlexCard to configure Publish Options. See Activate a FlexCard.

From the FlexCards tab, click a version of a FlexCard to open the FlexCard Designer.
From the FlexCard Designer submenu, click the down arrow next to Activate, and click Publish Options.
To configure metadata values, see Define Metadata Values from the FlexCard Designer.
To update the SVG resource with a custom icon, see Add a Custom Component SVG Icon to a FlexCard.

FlexCards Publish Options Properties
FlexCard Publish Options properties are configurable after activating a FlexCard. Define metadata values and update the SVG icon for your generated FlexCard LWC from the FlexCard Designer.

When publishing FlexCards, you have options for where and how the FlexCard is displayed. 
Define Metadata Values from the FlexCard Designer
Define the metadata values for the generated FlexCard LWC from the FlexCard Designer. When your FlexCard is active, use the Publish Options feature to configure API Version, Targets, Description, and other metadata values from a GUI or code editor.

Add a Custom Component SVG Icon to a FlexCard
Add an SVG resource as the custom icon for your generated LWC to easily identify it in the Lightning App Builder and the Experience Builder. Use the Publish Options feature on an activated FlexCard to update the default icon with a custom SVG resource.

What's next: Publish your FlexCard to a Lightning or Experience page. See Activate, Configure, and Publish FlexCards.
title: Configuring FlexCard Publish Options in OmniStudio
